== Overview == * In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|ja|陰陽五行説|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, Wu is associated with the yang aspect of the element {{ill|Earth (element)|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In Japan, it is also called "{{ill|Tsuchinoe|ja|つちのえ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}" (Elder Brother of Earth). * In terms of direction, it corresponds to the {{ill|Center|ja|中央|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Regarding time, it refers to around 4 a.m., with the period from 4 a.m. to 6 a.m. known as "{{ill|Boya|ja|戊夜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}." * The character "戊" is an {{ill|ideogram|ja|象形文字|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} representing a weapon resembling a battle-axe.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng| year=2014| title=Shuowen Xinzheng| location=Taipei| publisher=Yiwen Press| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| pages=962–93}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Rediscovery of Chinese Characters| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=102–105}}</ref> Its use to denote the fifth of the Ten Heavenly Stems is a case of {{ill|Jiajie|ja|仮借|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (phonetic loan). * When used in ordinal contexts, Wu represents the 5th position. * Years ending with the digit 8 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|西暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} are designated as Wu years. Another name for the Wu year is "{{ill|Zhuoyong|ja|著雍|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}" (also written as "{{ill|著雝|ja|著雝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}").<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations of Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, it is used in the names of compounds containing five carbon atoms, such as {{ill|Pentane|ja|ペンタン|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Pentyl group|ja|ペンチル基|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * Its counterpart is {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Mizunoto). * The {{ill|Lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} associated with Wu is south-southeast, slightly south (165 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoe (戊)==
{| class="wikitable alternance droite" |{{ill|Yang Earth Dragon|ja|戊辰|zh|戊辰|ko|무진|fr|Dragon de terre|de|Erde-Drache|en|Earth Dragon|lt=戊辰 (Yang Earth Dragon)|lt_ko=무진|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Tiger|ja|戊寅|zh|戊寅|ko|무인|fr|Tigre de terre|de|Erde-Tiger|en|Earth Tiger|lt=戊寅 (Yang Earth Tiger)|lt_ko=무인|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Rat|ja|戊子|zh|戊子|ko|무자|fr|Rat de terre|de|Erde-Ratte|en|Earth Rat|lt=戊子 (Yang Earth Rat)|lt_ko=무자|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Dog|ja|戊戌|zh|戊戌|ko|무술 (간지)|fr|Chien de terre|de|Erde-Hund|en|Earth Dog|lt=戊戌 (Yang Earth Dog)|lt_ko=무술|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Monkey|ja|戊申|zh|戊申|ko|무신|fr|Singe de terre|de|Erde-Affe|en|Earth Monkey|lt=戊申 (Yang Earth Monkey)|lt_ko=무신|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Horse|ja|戊午|zh|戊午|ko|무오|fr|Cheval de terre|de|Erde-Pferd|en|Earth Horse|lt=戊午 (Yang Earth Horse)|lt_ko=무오|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} |} == See Also == * [[戊辰戦争]] * {{prefix}} * {{intitle}}
