dar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} are designated as Wu years. Another name for the Wu year is "{{ill|Zhuoyong|ja|著雍|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhuoyong|qq=}}" (also written as "{{ill|著雝|ja|著雝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/著雝|qq=}}").<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations of Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=}}, it is used in the names of compounds containing five carbon atoms, such as {{ill|Pentane|ja|ペンタン|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Pentane|qq=}} and the {{ill|Pentyl group|ja|ペンチル基|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Pentyl group|qq=}}. * Its counterpart is {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gui|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoto (癸)|qq=}} (Mizunoto). * The {{ill|Lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} associated with Wu is south-southeast, slightly south (165 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoe (戊)==
