{{Ten Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches}} '''Wu''' (戊, bo, tsuchinoe) is the 5th of the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Ten Heavenly Stems]]. <ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=a602092fc003df5c0e16c71ef5b5a2fa1b5c015d65d986c106e397da1aa7e8afJmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoe+(%e6%88%8a)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjM0NA&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=b0de9cef7fbb919ba00edd65e5b6b759ce4515543c9394cfdbaa7bbe5e0c409cJmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoe+(%e6%88%8a)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmlob25nb21hc3Rlci5jb20vamFwYW5lc2UvZGljdGlvbmFyeS93b3JkLzU2MTkwL3RzdWNoaW5vZS1iby0lRTYlODglOEEtJUUzJTgxJUE0JUUzJTgxJUExJUUzJTgxJUFFJUUzJTgxJTg4LSVFMyU4MSVCQw&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=36c3b523c25f60637ea315b490ada1cd1c95eca16de8466a448a1c65722068a6JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Tsuchinoe+(%e6%88%8a)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9qbGVhcm4ubmV0L2RpY3Rpb25hcnkvJUU2JTg4JThB&ntb=1</ref>
It is different from the character [https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E6%88%89 戉].
== Pronunciations: 戊 (Stem 5) == * Chinese (Pinyin): Wù * Korean: Mu (무) * Vietnamese: Mậu * Japanese: ** On’yomi: Bo (ぼ) ** Elemental: Tsuchinoe (つちのえ, 土の兄 – “Elder Earth”)
== Overview == * In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|ja|陰陽五行説|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, Wu is associated with the yang aspect of the element {{ill|Earth (element)|ja|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|zh|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|zh|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)|lt=Earth (土)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth (element)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth (element)|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth (wuxing)|zh|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)|qq=}}. In Japan, it is also called "{{ill|Tsuchinoe|ja|つちのえ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoe|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoe|qq=}}" (Elder Brother of Earth). * In terms of direction, it corresponds to the [[:en:Chūō|Center]]. Regarding time, it refers to around 4 a.m., with the period from 4 a.m. to 6 a.m. known as "{{ill|Boya|ja|戊夜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boya|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boya|qq=}}." * The character "戊" is an {{ill|ideogram|ja|象形文字|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ideogram|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ideogram|qq=}} representing a weapon resembling a battle-axe.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng| year=2014| title=Shuowen Xinzheng| location=Taipei| publisher=Yiwen Press| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| pages=962–93|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Rediscovery of Chinese Characters| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=102–105|qq=}}</ref> Its use to denote the fifth of the Ten Heavenly Stems is a case of {{ill|Jiajie|ja|仮借|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jiajie|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jiajie|qq=}} (phonetic loan). * When used in ordinal contexts, Wu represents the 5th position. * Years ending with the digit 8 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] are designated as Wu years. Another name for the Wu year is "{{ill|Zhuoyong|ja|著雍|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhuoyong|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhuoyong|qq=}}" (also written as "{{ill|著雝|ja|著雝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/著雝|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/著雝|qq=}}").<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations of Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=}}, it is used in the names of compounds containing five carbon atoms, such as [[:en:Pentane|Pentane]] and the [[:en:Pentyl group|Pentyl group]]. * Its counterpart is {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|lt=Mizunoto (癸)|2=ja|3=癸|4=zh|5=癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gui|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoto (癸)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gui|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoto (癸)|qq=}} (Mizunoto). * The {{ill|Lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} associated with Wu is south-southeast, slightly south (165 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoe (戊)==
