|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. In Japan, it is also called "{{ill|Tsuchinoe|ja|つちのえ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoe|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoe|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}" (Elder Brother of Earth). * In terms of direction, it corresponds to the [[:en:Chūō|Center]]. Regarding time, it refers to around 4 a.m., with the period from 4 a.m. to 6 a.m. known as "{{ill|Boya|ja|戊夜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boya|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boya|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}." * The character "戊" is an {{ill|ideogram|ja|象形文字|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ideogram|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ideogram|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} representing a weapon resembling a battle-axe.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng| year=2014| title=Shuowen Xinzheng| location=Taipei| publisher=Yiwen Press| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| pages=962–93|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang| year=2022| title=Rediscovery of Chinese Characters| location=Shanghai| publisher=Shanghai Calligraphy and Painting Press| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=102–105|qq=}}</ref> Its use to denote the fifth of the Ten Heavenly Stems is a case of {{ill|Jiajie|ja|仮借|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jiajie|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jiajie|qq=}} (phonetic loan). * When used in ordinal contexts, Wu represents the 5th position. * Years ending with the digit 8 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] are designated as Wu years. Another name for the Wu year is "{{ill|Zhuoyong|ja|著雍|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhuoyong|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhuoyong|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}" (also written as "{{ill|著雝|ja|著雝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/著雝|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/著雝|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}").<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations of Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to IUPAC命名法}}, it is used in the names of compounds containing five carbon atoms, such as [[:en:Pentane|Pentane]] and the [[:en:Pentyl group|Pentyl group]]. * Its counterpart is {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|lt=Mizunoto (癸)|2=ja|3=癸|4=zh|5=癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gui|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoto (癸)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gui|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoto (癸)|qq=}} (Mizunoto). * The {{ill|Lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 歳徳神}} associated with Wu is south-southeast, slightly south (165 degrees). ==Sexagenary cycles containing Tsuchinoe (戊)== {{wiktionary|戊}} {| class="wikitable alternance droite" |{{ill|Yang Earth Dragon|ja|戊辰|1=Yang Earth Dragon|zh|戊辰|1=Yang Earth Dragon|ko|무진|fr|Dragon de terre|de|Erde-Drache|en|Earth Dragon|lt=戊辰 (Yang Earth Dragon)|lt_ko=무진|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Earth Dragon|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Earth Dragon|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Earth Dragon|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yang Earth Tiger|